die, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mathilde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."],"variants":[{"name":"Mechtild","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]},{"name":"Matilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]},{"name":"Mechtilde","meanings":["from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mathilde de ROSIÈRES was born in 1253, in Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, François de Rosières en Santerre, was 34 and her mother, Jehanne DE PERONNE-DE CORBIE, was 20. She married Othon III D'ENCRE-D'AILLY SUR NOYE in 1268, in Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1309, in Albert, Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1253–1309":"1253–1309","1255–1313":"1255–1313","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1245–1299":"1245–1299","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","1275–1329":"1275–1329","1219–1281":"1219–1281","1233–1256":"1233–1256","1253":"1253","1275":"1275","1281":"1281","Abt 1252":"umbes 1252","1313":"1313","1268":"1268","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1299":"1299","1233":"1233","1255":"1255","1309":"1309","1219":"1219","1329":"1329","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Albert, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Albert, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Europa":"Europe","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1253–1309":"1253–1309","1255–1313":"1255–1313","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1245–1299":"1245–1299","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","1275–1329":"1275–1329","1219–1281":"1219–1281","1233–1256":"1233–1256","1253":"1253","1275":"1275","1281":"1281","Abt 1252":"noin 1252","1313":"1313","1268":"1268","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1299":"1299","1233":"1233","1255":"1255","1309":"1309","1219":"1219","1329":"1329","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Albert, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Albert, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Europa":"Europe","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1253–1309":"1253–1309","1255–1313":"1255–1313","1245–Male":"1245–Décédé","1245–1299":"1245–1299","1275–Male":"1275–Décédé","1275–1329":"1275–1329","1219–1281":"1219–1281","1233–1256":"1233–1256","1253":"1253","1275":"1275","1281":"1281","Abt 1252":"environ 1252","1313":"1313","1268":"1268","1256":"1256","124